rComments: I'm sure he's a great guy, but I don't feel like I got anything out of his class other than course credit. He has a tendency to ramble on and on without making any clear points, and his grading system is very subjective. He gives lackluster feedback, but he doesn't grade too hard. Readings are long and confusing.

rComments: He genuinely cares students in his class do well. Even though he was not an easy marker, he was a fair marker. He makes the lectures interesting. Funny guy. Would take another class by him.

Amazing person and prof, this seminar was an unexpected gem -- I don't think I would have taken such an interest in the class had it been taught by another instructor. Super nice and clearly interested in student learning -- as long as you do the readings and participate, you'll enjoy the material, the lectures, and the class!
Super nice guy and very detailed when he lectures. Participation/attendance is a huge part of the grade. Marks nicely but not easy. gives good critical feedback.

rComments: Awesome Professor. Lectures and tutorials are extremely important, and if you have a propensity of skipping you won't pass. Overall great person who is clearly very knowledgeable in political theory.

rComments: Professor Shoikhedbrod created amazing lectures which would compliment the readings (some of which were difficult) and ensured that students comprehended the material. He was very approachable (which was helpful if you had any quick questions) and held office hours regularly. Lastly, tutorials allowed you to discuss materials and ask questions.
